<article>
    <h1>Trial of Po&#xAD;lice Bea&#xAD;con in parks to keep vis&#xAD;i&#xAD;tors safe</h1>
    <h2>Struc&#xAD;ture, now on trial for a year, en&#xAD;ables of&#xAD;fi&#xAD;cers to ob&#xAD;serve and talk to park vis&#xAD;i&#xAD;tors</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201214/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-14"><time>2020-12-14</time></a>
        - <span>THE BIG STORY</span>
        - <span role="byline">Cara Wong cara&#xAD;wong@sph.com.sg</span>
    </section>

    <p>To en­hance po­lice pres­ence and en­able quick in­ter­ven­tion in park con­nec­tors, the po­lice are tri­alling a new tech­nol­ogy struc­ture – the</p>
    <p>Po­lice Bea­con. Com­pris­ing closed-cir­cuit tele­vi­sion cam­eras and a com­mu­ni­ca­tions but­ton linked to the po­lice op­er­a­tions com­mand cen­tre, the bea­con makes it pos­si­ble for of­fi­cers in the com­mand cen­tre to ob­serve and talk to park­go­ers.</p>
    <p>To en­hance po­lice pres­ence and en­able quick in­ter­ven­tion in park con­nec­tors, the po­lice are tri­alling a new tech­nol­ogy struc­ture that will al­low park­go­ers to ask for and re­ceive help quickly.</p>
    <p>The Po­lice Bea­con, a struc­ture com­pris­ing closed-cir­cuit tele­vi­sion (CCTV) cam­eras and a com­mu­ni­ca­tions but­ton linked to the po­lice op­er­a­tions com­mand cen­tre, makes it pos­si­ble for of­fi­cers in the com­mand cen­tre to ob­serve and talk to park­go­ers.</p>
    <p>The first bea­con pro­to­type was launched last Fri­day at the Pung­gol Water­way park con­nec­tor by Min­is­ter of State for Home Af­fairs Des­mond Tan.</p>
    <p>The sec­ond pro­to­type at Sengkang River­side Park will be op­er­a­tional by the end of this month.</p>
    <p>Be­sides com­mu­ni­ca­tion ca­pa­bil­i­ties, the struc­ture also has warn­ing fea­tures such as a siren, speak­ers, blink­ers and flood­lights.</p>
    <p>In ad­di­tion, the bea­con has an au­to­mated ex­ter­nal de­fib­ril­la­tor, with the po­lice re­ceiv­ing an alert when mem­bers of the pub­lic ac­cess it. Of­fi­cers at the com­mand cen­tre will then as­sess the sit­u­a­tion and mo­bilise emer­gency med­i­cal ser­vices as re­quired.</p>
    <p>An elec­tronic screen at­tached to the bea­con dis­plays crime preven­tion mes­sages.</p>
    <p>The po­lice will mon­i­tor calls and live video feed from the struc­ture at a sep­a­rate work­sta­tion in the com­mand cen­tre.</p>
    <p>Mr Tan said the bea­con al­lows for “im­me­di­ate mit­i­ga­tion of in­ci­dents” through warn­ing sys­tems, such as the ac­ti­va­tion of flood­lights and pub­lic an­nounce­ments.</p>
    <p>“This will hope­fully al­low mem­bers of the pub­lic to have some as­sur­ance that the po­lice are sup­port­ing them while the re­sponse team tries to ar­rive as soon as pos­si­ble,” he said dur­ing the launch event last Fri­day.</p>
    <p>Deputy Su­per­in­ten­dent (DSP) Lionel Lee, op­er­a­tions of­fi­cer in the po­lice’s Fu­ture Op­er­a­tions and Plan­ning Di­vi­sion, said park con­nec­tors were cho­sen as the ar­eas are rel­a­tively more se­cluded and have fewer CCTVs.</p>
    <p>The po­lice al­ready have a strong pres­ence in crowded ar­eas such as the Or­chard Road belt, which is well cov­ered by surveil­lance tech­nol­ogy and po­lice pa­trols, he said.</p>
    <p>He added that both pro­to­types will be tri­alled for a year. If the trial is a suc­cess, the force will look into de­ploy­ing more bea­cons in park con­nec­tors and pub­lic spa­ces.</p>
    <p>The bea­con tech­nol­ogy was de­vel­oped in col­lab­o­ra­tion with the Home Team Sci­ence and Tech­nol­ogy Agency (HTX) over the past year. Although the bea­con’s com­po­nents are not new, HTX’s Vic­tor</p>
    <p>Yuen, head of op­er­a­tions sys­tems in the agency’s Polic­ing Pro­gramme Man­age­ment Cen­tre, said the in­no­va­tion here lies in in­te­grat­ing such tech­nol­ogy into the po­lice’s work­flow.</p>
    <p>DSP Lee added: “The Sin­ga­pore Po­lice Force will con­tinue to ex­plore and adopt tech­nol­ogy that en­hances our ca­pa­bil­i­ties to keep Sin­ga­pore safe and se­cure.”</p>

